---
summary: When matrix.org is down, many folks are stranded. How can we help them?
---
created: 2015-09-16 09:57:37.0
creator: neb
description: |-
  Submitted by @matthew:matrix.org
  When matrix.org's VM fell over the other day, lots of people asked what backup server we can connect to. In practice I think they just want an alternative public server they can create an account on and use - obviously we don't have decentralised accounts or HA between synapses yet. We advertise oddvar.org on the wiki page, but I'm not sure it's being maintained - we could perhaps have an official backup.matrix.org HS or something for this purpose
